"```sql\nSELECT loan.loan_id, district.A2 AS district_name, district.A11 AS average_salary\nFROM loan\nJOIN account ON loan.account_id = account.account_id\nJOIN district ON account.district_id = district.district_id\nWHERE loan.duration = 60;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the loan ID, district name, and average salary for loans with a duration of 60 months. It joins the `loan`, `account`, and `district` tables using the foreign key relationships defined in the schema. The `district.A2` column is used to get the district name, and `district.A11` is used to get the average salary."